Authoritative context to apply in every new chat:

Strategy model (intraday only, Dhan broker):
- EMA Fast=20, EMA Slow=50 on close; both on 5m and 15m
- RSI period=14 (Wilder smoothing via EWM com=13, adjust=False); LONG if RSI>50, SHORT if RSI<50
- VWAP intraday reset daily; typical price=(H+L+C)/3; applied on 5m only
- Volume filter: `volume_ratio = volume / SMA(volume, 20)`, require `volume_ratio >= 1.5`
- EMA crossover freshness: occurred within last 3 candles

Trading windows (IST):
- Trade only in `09:30–11:30` OR `13:30–14:45`
- Time stop/force exit: `14:45`

15-min market structure (every bar):
- trending_up: EMA20_15m > EMA50_15m AND close_15m > VWAP_15m (LONG setups)
- trending_down: EMA20_15m < EMA50_15m AND close_15m < VWAP_15m (SHORT setups)
- otherwise: ranging => NO TRADE

Entry (13 gates; all must be TRUE):
- Gate 2: trades_taken_today < 2
- Gate 3: consecutive_losses < 2
- Gate 4: daily_pnl > -(capital * 0.06)
- Gate 6: EMA20_5m crossed above/below EMA50_5m within last 3 candles
- Gate 7: close_5m > VWAP_5m (LONG) / close_5m < VWAP_5m (SHORT)
- Gate 8: RSI_5m > 50 (LONG) / RSI_5m < 50 (SHORT)
- Gate 10: VIX not < 12 if VIX feed enabled (skip when VIX < 12)
- Gate 11: no open position
- Gate 12: SL distance > 0; Gate 13: calculated_quantity >= 1

Risk/VIX adjustments:
- Risk per trade: 3% of capital, but if VIX > 20 then risk is halved to 1.5%
- If VIX < 12: skip trade entirely
- Max trades/day: 2; Max consecutive losses: 2

Options translation:
- LONG => Buy ATM Call (CE); SHORT => Buy ATM Put (PE)
- Strike interval: 50 points; weekly expiry preference (Thursday)
- VIX > 20 => ATM only; VIX <= 20 => allow 1 OTM strike (lower cost)

SL / Target (hard formulas):
- LONG: SL = MIN(signal_low, prev_low); Target = Entry + (SL_dist * 1.5)
- SHORT: SL = MAX(signal_high, prev_high); Target = Entry - (SL_dist * 1.5)

Implementation constraints:
- Keep these rules consistent with `README.md` and `NIFTY50_BOT_SPEC.md`.
- Match existing code style; do not add new dependencies unless explicitly requested.
